{"id":16366,"title":"[Definition of \"Safety and Hygiene Packages\" as a management model for the Hospital Hygiene Service (HHS)].","abstract":"The purpose of this research is to identify and formalize the Hospital Hygiene Service activities and products, evaluating them in a cost accounting management view. The ultimate aim, is to evaluate the financial adverse events prevention impact, in an Hospital Hygiene Service management. A three step methodology based on affinity grouping activities, was employed. This methodology led us to identify 4 action areas, with 23 related productive processes, and 86 available safety packages. Owing to this new methodology, we was able to implement a systematic evaluation of the furnished services. ","date":"2014-07-10","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25008222","annotations":[{"name":"Research","weight":0.695164,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Research"},{"name":"Management","weight":0.636795,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Management"},{"name":"Accountancy","weight":0.566639,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Accountancy"},{"name":"Finance","weight":0.479186,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Finance"},{"name":"Safety","weight":0.445113,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Safety"},{"name":"Methodology","weight":0.395417,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Methodology"},{"name":"Hospital","weight":0.320576,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hospital"},{"name":"Hygiene","weight":0.18053,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hygiene"},{"name":"Evaluation","weight":0.107046,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evaluation"},{"name":"Productivity","weight":0.0750165,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Productivity"},{"name":"Preventive medicine","weight":0.070554,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Preventive_medicine"},{"name":"Definition","weight":0.0391252,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Definition"},{"name":"United States Department of Health and Human Services","weight":0.0391252,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Department_of_Health_and_Human_Services"},{"name":"Model (person)","weight":0.0301868,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Model_(person)"},{"name":"Adverse effect","weight":0.0300804,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adverse_effect"},{"name":"Cost accounting","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cost_accounting"},{"name":"Accounting management","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Accounting_management"},{"name":"Formal system","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Formal_system"},{"name":"Systematics","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Systematics"},{"name":"Action theory (philosophy)","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Action_theory_(philosophy)"},{"name":"Product (business)","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Product_(business)"},{"name":"Business process","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Business_process"},{"name":"Railways Act 1921","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Railways_Act_1921"},{"name":"Service management","weight":0.0140524,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Service_management"}]}
